Press Trust of IndiaMonday , 19 September 2011 16 : 40 Gangtok : At least 50 people , including 23 in Sikkim , have been killed in a powerful earthquake on Sunday that triggered widespread landslides and road blockages making rescue work on Monday more difficult in the worst - hit Himalayan state . Another eight people , who were travelling in a bus of Teesta Urja Limited , are presumed dead as their vehicle got stuck under the debris of a landslide caused by the 6 . 8 magnitude tremblor last evening , Major General S L Narasimhan , GOC 17 Mountain Division , told reporters here . The overnight toll climbed to 50 , with 23 people being killed in Sikkim , six in West Bengal , seven each in Bihar , Nepal and Tibet , official reports said .